==English==

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''godmother''' (''plural'' '''[[godmothers]]''')

# A woman present at the [[christening]] of a baby who promises to help raise the child in a [[Christian]] manner; a female [[godparent]] who sponsors the [[baptism]] of a child.

====Translations====
*Slovak: [[krstná mama]] ''f'' (reflects the relationship to the baptized child); [[kmotra#Slovak|kmotra]] ''f'' (reflects the relationship to the parents of the baptized child, not to the child)

